column1: Note 1: For most 8- and 16-bit devices all the following use the same registers/resources: hardware breakpoints; data captures; runtime watches.
For example: if you use a data capture resource for a symbol you will not be able to use a hardware breakpoint or runtime watch resource for that symbol.
For most PIC32 devices all the following use the same registers/resources: data captures; runtime watches. Hardware breakpoints use different resources.
For example: if you use a data capture resource for a symbol you will not be able to use a runtime watch resource for that symbol and vice versa.
